
<purchabr>DOWTY</purchabr> TO BUY <sellerabr>BOEING</sellerabr> UNIT FOR <dlramt>42.5 MLN DLRS</dlramt>
    LONDON, June 16 - <purchaser>Dowty Group Plc</purchaser> {<purchcode>DWTY.L</purchcode>} said it <status>agreed
to buy</status> {<acquired>Hydraulic Units Inc</acquired>} from <seller>Boeing Co</seller> {<sellercode>BA.N</sellercode>} for around
<dlramt>42.5 mln dlrs</dlramt> cash.
    The final sum payable would be adjusted according to
changes in net tangible assets between March 29 and completion,
due on July 1. Payment would be financed through medium-term
borrowings.
    <acqabr>Hydraulic</acqabr> reported 4.3 mln dlrs pretax profit in the year
to end-December 1986 on sales of 53.2 mln. It designs,
manufactures and sells <acqbus>hydraulic and mechanical systems</acqbus> to
airframe manufacturers.
